  "texts": [
    "Recall, these are composed of just those movements most causally proximate to the items in the inner cognitive economy that constitute agent's basic reasons while still being attributable to her as exercises of her rational agency.",
    "They relate to components of a putative wider whole action (e.g., 'the movements of the laces') as causes to effects.",
    "The smaller units must be actions, however, since the agent must perform these if she is to imprint her intentions onto the world -the alternative would be an end to which she takes no means or a basic action that does not include her body.",
    "Since both of these options are unacceptable, basic actions are actions; and so, any time an agent acts, what she does is at least a basic action.",
    "At this point, the Strict Bodily Constraint follows from an application of the A-D Principle: all actions are identical with basic actions because the principle identifies what the agent does by doing something else with a single event."
  ],
